The paper deals with interference elimination in wireless communication systems, which is a topic that falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of multiple antennas and their spacing, which is related to the Signal Processing (cs.SY) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a practical implementation of the scheme, which involves selecting appropriate antennas from a large linear antenna array, which falls under the Mathematics of Computing (cs.MA) sub-category.
